{"lemma":"رَمَقُ","slug":"رَمَقُ","root":"ر.م.ق","root_slug":"ر-م-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-م-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16671","n16673","n16679"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"last breath (of life)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to glance at, to see faintly, to survey"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16671","headword_ar":"رَمَقٌ","root":"rmq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the spirit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the soul;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, TA;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last breath:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and applied also to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromaAqN","text_ar":"اَرْمَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) It is said that a man in a case of necessity may eat of that which has died a natural death"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAyasud~u Alr~amaqa","text_ar":"مَايَسُدُّ الرَّمَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What will stay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrest, the remains of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what will maintain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preserve, the strength."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [In like manner, also,] one says, of sustenance,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yumosiku Alr~amaqa","text_ar":"يُمْسِكُ الرَّمَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It stays,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrests, the remains of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"maintains the strength"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumoqapN","text_ar":"رُمْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A flock of sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herd of goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) a Pers. word, (S,) arabicized, (S, K,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaho","text_ar":"رَمَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","K","S","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n16673","headword_ar":"رُمُقٌ","root":"rmq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", a pl., signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poor"},{"kind":"text","text":"men,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who are satisfied with little sustenance, such as suffices to stay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrest, the remains of life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to maintain the strength:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"envying"},{"kind":"text","text":"persons: sing. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAmiqN","text_ar":"رَامِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramuwqN","text_ar":"رَمُوقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, K, TA:) which signifies one."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who looks at men from the outer angle of the eye and with envy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n16679","headword_ar":"رُمَّقٌ","root":"rmq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) applied to a man. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}